				<reportElement x="0" y="-20" width="572" height="670" uuid="d504ada0-e2c1-4c97-b26a-c6fa055fed26"/>
				<text><![CDATA[THIS  LEASE  AGREEMENT is made the date on section 11 of this agreement, BETWEEN MOREPLEX TV Ltd, a limited liability company duly incorporated under the laws of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, with registered office address at NO 15B KUDIRAT ABIOLA WAY, IKEJA, LAGOS  NIGERIA (hereinafter called ‘COMPANY’ and shall for the sake of this agreement be referred to as ‘The Company’ which expression shall where the context permits include its successors-in-title, privies and assigns) of the first part; AND
		 with address_____________________________________________________________________________________________ (hereinafter referred to as  “The Customer” which expression shall where the context permits include its successors-in-title, privies and assigns) of the other part.
WHEREAS 
    1. The Company is the owner and operator of a Direct –To – Home Satellite platform known as MOREPLEX TV and is desirous of maintaining and smoothly operating same and to give out its Decoders to interested customers for lease The Customer  has presented to the company his  willingness  in taking the company’s products for lease and capacity to pay the agreed total sum in the manner as in Section 11 of this agreement.
    2. Parties have agreed and as such willfully, without duress entered into this agreement. 
    3. The company reserves the right to make adjustment on this agreement from time to time to the benefit of both parties.
    NOW THIS AGREEMENT WITNESSES AS FOLLOWS. 
    1. QUALIFICATION 
The Customer haven been qualified through an online verification process with the payment of  non-refundable fee of N1,000.00 (One thousand Naira ) ONLY   as Processing / logistic fee. The company will issue a decoder to customer with terms of payment as stated in section 11 below. All payments shall be made to the designated account numbers as provided by the company.
The customer agrees to be responsible for payments until paid in full and will forfeit any discount given should  Customer default.
The Customer shall indemnify and hold harmless the company from any and all fines, damages, losses, costs and expenses(including reasonable attorneys’ fees) incurred by the Company as a breach of this agreement by the Customer
    2. THE COMPANY COVENANTS AS FOLLOWS
i. The company shall make available to the customer lease agreement and other necessary forms (if any) at the company’s head office, or the dealer offices, or online  .
ii. The Company shall try to make the process swift and ensure that customer  takes delivery of their products  in their different locations especially for the online customers.
iii. The company shall be available at all times to offer technical advice and consultation on issues relating to the content and subject matter of this agreement.
iv. The customer agrees and accepts that online acknowledgement, or scanned document/signature, or electronic signature for this agreement, which is adopted to make the process swift, is legally binding on customer. 
 CUSTOMER  COVENANTS AS FOLLOW:
    i. The Customer shall read the Lease agreement and any other form /forms   thoroughly and provide the CORRECT details needed therein.
    ii. The Customer shall provide His/her bank details, including the BVN and the NIN numbers.
    iii. The Customer shall provide Valid means of identification
    iv. The Customer shall make available any proof of capacity for example,  a copy of the office I.D cards for the working class customers  , a copy of Business registration certificate  for the business class customers, a reliable guarantor and  verifiable addresses . 
    v. The Customer   shall provide functional phone lines , email addresses and verifiable address and agrees to readily update any that changes.
    vi. The Customer shall give the Company unrestrained access to his/her accounts ONLY for the purpose of RECOVERY of the agreed sum  for the stipulated number of months  agreed by parties which includes but not limited to writing /signing  a debit note or order to his/her bank / banks.
    vii. The Customer  shall report faulty set top boxes within 2 days of discovery of such fault to the company  or to the  nearest Company’s  Dealer, whereas the company shall not be responsible for any willful, careless, negligent act or omission occasioning the fault or damage to the set top boxes while in the custody of the Customer.
    viii. Set up boxes already worked on or whose warranties have been broken or removed shall not be received or accepted by the company and as such shall not be replaced. ]]></text>
