				<text><![CDATA[     
    3. DELIVERY
Unless the parties agree otherwise, all products ordered by the Customer shall be sent to the Customer within a day before the expected date of delivery depending on the customers location but not later than 5 working days ,  except for unforeseen logistic related   issues which  goes beyond the Company’s  control  of which the Customer will be duly notified.

Where the Customer designates an agent, a common carrier or representative (recipient) for delivery of ordered products and such products are passed to such recipient, the risk of loss and damages to the product shall pass to the Customer upon delivery of such product to the recipient designated by him/her.

All claims for non-conforming deliveries must be made in writing to the company or to the nearest Dealer   within ten (10) days of the passing of the risk of loss and damages, as described above. Any claim not made within such period shall be deemed waived and released. The customer shall be responsible for any shipping charges to deliver the decoder to the customer.
    4. LIMITED WARRANTY
The Customer acknowledges that all components of the products are being manufactured for the Company by subcontractors or other entities other than the Company. Company extends to the Customer the warranties as to such components provided by such other entities to the Company for the length of time that such warranty remains valid for the company. There shall not be implied warranties
    5. LIMITATION ON LIABILITIES
The Company’s liability arising out of the manufacture, sale or supplying of the products or their use or disposition, whether based upon warranty, contract, tort or otherwise, shall not exceed the actual purchase price paid by the Customer for the product.

In no event shall the Company be liable to the Customer or any other person or entity for special, incidental or consequential damages (including but not limited to loss of data or use damages) arising out of the manufacture, sale or supply of the products, even if the Company has been advised of the possibility of such damages or losses. 
    6. FORCE MAJEURE
Neither the Company nor the Customer shall be liable in damages, or shall be subject to termination of this agreement by the other party, for any delay or default in performing any obligation hereunder if that delay or default is due to any cause beyond the reasonable control and without fault of negligence of that party. 
    7. INDEMNIFICATION
The Customer hereby agrees to indemnify, defend and hold harmless the company, its affiliates and all officers, directors, employees and agents thereof (hereinafter referred to as ‘indemnities’) from all liabilities, claims, damages, losses, cost, expenses, demands, suits and actions(including without limitation  to attorneys’ fees and settlement costs) (collectively, ‘Damages’) arising out of or related to damage or injury to property or persons, or to any representations of the Customer not authorized hereunder. 

    8. TERM
The term of this agreement shall commence from the execution date or a date as may be agreed by the parties and subject to termination on a later date by either party pursuant to the provisions herein.
    9. TERMINATION
This agreement automatically terminates once the Customer   finishes his/her payment of the agreed sum of which the company acknowledges same. 
    10. GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION
This agreement and any dispute or claim about it or its subject matter is governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Federal Republic of Nigeria.]]></text>
